#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.263"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.263:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.263:0.2"
msgid "26. Abhiññāvagga"
msgstr "26. Insight"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: sāvajja-anavajjasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.263:0.3"
msgid "263. Kammasutta"
msgstr "263. Deeds"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.253"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.263:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso khataṃ "
"upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca "
"apuññaṃ pasavati."
msgstr ""
"“When a foolish, incompetent bad person has four qualities they keep "
"themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by "
"sensible people, and they make much bad karma."

msgctxt "an4.263:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.263:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sāvajjena kāyakammena, sāvajjena vacīkammena, sāvajjena manokammena, "
"sāvajjāya diṭṭhiyā—"
msgstr ""
"Blameworthy deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, and blameworthy view."

msgctxt "an4.263:1.4"
msgid ""
"imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato bālo abyatto asappuriso "
"khataṃ upahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, sāvajjo ca hoti sānuvajjo viññūnaṃ, "
"bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavati."
msgstr ""
"When a foolish, incompetent bad person has these four qualities they keep "
"themselves broken and damaged. They deserve to be blamed and criticized by "
"sensible people, and they make much bad karma."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.263:2.1"
msgid ""
"Catūhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso akkhataṃ "
"anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo viññūnaṃ, bahuñca "
"puññaṃ pasavati."
msgstr ""
"When an astute, competent good person has four qualities they keep "
"themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized "
"by sensible people, and they make much merit."

msgctxt "an4.263:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.263:2.3"
msgid ""
"Anavajjena kāyakammena, anavajjena vacīkammena, anavajjena manokammena, "
"anavajjāya diṭṭhiyā—"
msgstr "Blameless deeds by way of body, speech, and mind, and blameless view."

msgctxt "an4.263:2.4"
msgid ""
"imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito viyatto sappuriso "
"akkhataṃ anupahataṃ attānaṃ pariharati, anavajjo ca hoti ananuvajjo "
"viññūnaṃ, bahuñca puññaṃ pasavatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"When an astute, competent good person has these four qualities they keep "
"themselves healthy and whole. They don’t deserve to be blamed and criticized "
"by sensible people, and they make much merit.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.263:2.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.263:2.6"
msgid "Abhiññāvaggo chaṭṭho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.263:3.1"
msgid "Abhiññā pariyesanā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.263:3.2"
msgid "saṅgahaṃ mālukyaputto;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.263:3.3"
msgid "Kulaṃ dve ca ājānīyā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.263:3.4"
msgid "balaṃ araññakammunāti."
msgstr ""
